SIMPLE: inferior
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inferior
<hw>In*fe"ri*or</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L., compar. of
<ets>inferus</ets> that is below, underneath, the lower; akin to E.
<ets>under</ets>: cf. F. <ets>inf⟦eacute⟧rieur</ets>. See
<er>Under</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Lower in place, rank, value, excellence, etc.; less
important or valuable; subordinate; underneath; beneath.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A thousand <qex>inferior</qex> and particular propositions.</q>
<rj><qau>I. Watts.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The body, or, as some love to call it, our <qex>inferior</qex>
nature.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whether they are equal or <qex>inferior</qex> to my other poems,
an author is the most improper judge.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Poor or mediocre; <as>as, an <ex>inferior</ex>
quality of goods</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Nearer the sun
than the earth is; <as>as, the <ex>inferior</ex> or interior planets; an
<ex>inferior</ex> conjunction of Mercury or Venus.</as></def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>Below the horizon; <as>as, the <ex>inferior</ex> part
of a meridian</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Situated below some
other organ; -- said of a calyx when free from the ovary, and therefore
below it, or of an ovary with an adherent and therefore inferior
calyx.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>On the side of a flower which is next the
bract; anterior.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Junior or subordinate in rank;
<as>as, an <ex>inferior</ex> officer</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Inferior court</b></col> <fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>a court
subject to the jurisdiction of another court known as the
<contr>superior court</contr>, or <contr>higher court</contr>.</cd> --
<mcol><col><b>Inferior letter</b></col>, <col><b>Inferior
figure</b></col></mcol> <fld>(Print.)</fld>, <cd>a small letter or
figure standing at the bottom of the line (opposed to <contr>superior
letter</contr> or <xex>figure</xex>), <as>as in A<subs>2</subs>,
B<subs>n</subs>, 2 and <it>n</it> are <ex>inferior</ex>
characters</as>.</cd> -- <col><b>Inferior tide</b></col>, <cd>the tide
corresponding to the moon's transit of the meridian, when below the
horizon.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inferior</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Inferior
<hw>In*fe"ri*or</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A person lower in station,
rank, intellect, etc., than another.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A great person gets more by obliging his <qex>inferior</qex> than
by disdaining him.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inferiority</ent>⟦br⟧
